					   <td>

			
			
			



<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2"><b>MMORPG News</b> - BSI Sues Mythic for MMORPG's Player's Rights</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=554640" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    Black Snow Interactive, a company dedicated to buying and selling MMORPG items has filed a lawsuit against one of the top MMOPRG developers, Mythic, the makers of Dark Age of Camelot.  This lawsuit could perhaps have a ground breaking effect on the entire MMORPG market.
<blockquote>
  <h2><font size="3" face="Verdana">BLACKSNOW INTERACTIVE SUES MYTHIC (DAOC) IN 
  FEDERAL COURT FOR MMORPG PLAYER’S RIGHTS</font></h2>
  </b></font><font face="Arial" size="2">
  <p><font face="Verdana" size="2">Mythic Entertainment is named as the 
  defendant in this case filed on February 5th 11:50AM involving various 
  anti-trust, copyright, and anti-competitive issues. BlackSnow Interactive 
  (BSI) is a group of individuals that play, buy, and sell in various Massively 
  Multiplayer Online Role Playing Games (MMORPG). Growing from only one person 
  nearly two years ago, to seven full-time people, this group has successfully 
  developed a market in which they are able to supply players with gaming 
  currency, items, or characters at competitive prices. Mythic wants BSI to 
  cease all sales immediately. </p>
  </font><font face="arial" size="3">
  <p><font size="2" face="Verdana">After entering the DAoC market, shortly after 
  its release, BSI created a website and began listing their sales on various 
  auction sites, such as Ebay. BSI’s Director of Sales, Lee Caldwell, was quoted 
  as saying, “What it comes down to is, does a MMORPG player have rights to his 
  time, or does Mythic own that player’s time? It is unfair of Mythic to stop 
  those who wish to sell their items, currency or even their own accounts, which 
  were created with their own time. Mythic, in my opinion, and hopefully the 
  court’s, does not have the copyright ownership to regulate what a player does 
  with his or her own time or to determine how much that time is worth on the 
  free market.“ </font></p>
  <p><font size="2" face="Verdana">Caldwell goes on to say, “Mythic’s attempt to 
  stifle competition in their own game makes it possible for only full-time 
  gamers to succeed in the game and most MMORPG players can’t compete on that 
  level. The person that plays just a few hours a week, can’t put in the time 
  required to build their character or collect the items needed to join others 
  in the online battles. No one has stood up to any of these software giants, 
  until now.” </font></p>
  <p><font size="2" face="Verdana">If you would like to take a look at the 
  actual court document, please visit </font>
  <a href="http://www.camelotexchange.com" style="font-family: Verdana; text-decoration: underline">
  <font size="2">www.camelotexchange.com</font></a><font size="2" face="Verdana">.
  </font></p>
  <p><font size="2" face="Verdana">Contact information for BlackSnow 
  Interactive: </font></p>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
