			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				This is likely one of the dumbest things I've ever had the misfortune of seeing on the Internet.<BR>
<BR>
This case won't make it before a jury.  Intellectual property/copywrite/trademark etc cases usually go before a judge, or a panel of judges, because the laws surrounding these issues are so convoluted and complex that it would be hard to find a random panel of jurors who had the neccessary education to preside over a trial.<BR>
<BR>
That said, and as everyone has said, it's in the freakin EULA that you can't do what they do.  It REALLY should be Mythic taking BSI to court.  They've gone far beyond the individual breaching the EULA, BSI is a company founded in the spirit of doing so.<BR>
<BR>
EBay, etc ruins games.  Period.  Spoiled little brats with daddy's credit card prancing about in gear they didn't earned proclaiming their greatness are far too common.  On the flip side of that coin, people who take loot from a group of people or an individual who could use it, in order to sell it on &quot;Ebay&quot;, ruin the grouping-community on every game.<BR>
<BR>
They have a &quot;1-800&quot; number up on their site.  I encourage everyone who reads this to call that number, and tell them just how rediculous they are.  Tell them also, that you clogging up their sales line, is the off-game equivalent of spawn-monopolizing while they farm gear to sell.  <BR>
<BR>
I just called it... some dude answered, I said, &quot;Hey, are you one of those morons sueing Mythic?&quot;  *click*<BR>
<BR>
Guess he didn't want to talk about it.<BR>
<BR>
The number is:  1-888-491-4949<BR>
<BR>
Have fun!
				</font>
			</td>

